Teltoli looked at her friend, amused as the raptor chuckled to 
herself about something she had remembered. What, she would probably 
never know.

The Fuzor listened to what Carnage had to say, and nodded to herself. 
She, Teltoli, had never been good at words, but that was more or less 
what her purpouses were.. she guessed. 

"Night, Carnage.. and.. Thanks" She grinned, and closed her eyes, 
letting out a big breath. Tomorrow was going to be a big day, so she 
may as well get a good nights sleep!

However, try as she might, the noises of the forest kept her awake. 
She put her paws over her ears, but that resulted in a very 
uncomfortable position. She groaned quietly and turned over on her 
side, and shut her ears. A small smile crept across her face, looking 
the picture of innocence in her sleep.
